<p itemprop="description">Network technologies involves understanding and implementing various networking protocols, hardware, and software solutions to enable reliable and secure communications across government networks.</p>

<div class="proficiency-levels">
    <h2>Proficiency Levels</h2>

    <ol class="skill-levels">
        <li>
            <h3>Awareness</h3>
            <p>You can understand basic networking concepts and recognise different network technologies and their applications in government environments.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h3>Working</h3>
            <p>You can configure and maintain network equipment, implement network protocols, and troubleshoot common network issues following established procedures.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h3>Practitioner</h3>
            <p>You can design and implement complex network solutions, optimize network performance, and evaluate new network technologies for government adoption.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h3>Expert</h3>
            <p>You can lead network technology strategy, establish technology standards, and drive innovation in government network infrastructure and services.</p>
        </li>
    </ol>
</div>

